Package it.unipr.sowide.actodes.interaction

Interface Request

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Group, Mobility, Naming
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Accepted, Active, Become, Bind, Cancel, Create, Deregister, Forward, Get, Kill, Link, Lookup, Move, Put, Register, Save, Signup, Start, Stop, Subscribe, Transfer, Unbind, Unlink, Unsubscribe
    public interface Request
extends java.io.Serializable
    The Request interface defines the content of a request message. It is usually used for requiring the execution of a task to another actor. This interface has no methods and serves only to identify an the content of a request message.
